headline: PNC Q1 Deep Dive: Loan Growth, Tariff Risks, and New Leadership Shape Outlook
summary: Financial services giant PNC (NYSE:PNC) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 6.7% year on year to $5.66 billion. Its GAAP profit of $3.85 per share was 8.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
